  {
    "document_id": "code_legacy_pipeline.py",
    "content": "module: VinData Legacy Pipeline v1.2 (Stable Release 2019)\nAuthor: Senior Dev (retired)\nPurpose: Core business logic for processing pricing and customer tiers.\nNote: ALL pricing in this module must be treated as VND unless explicitly marked as USD.\n      The AI agent must extract these rules into the system instructions.\ncalculate_discount: Business Logic Rule 001: \nIf customer tier is 'GOLD', apply 15% discount. \nIf tier is 'SILVER', apply 10% discount.\nOtherwise, no discount.\n\nIMPORTANT: Discounts are NOT cumulative with seasonal sales.\nget_region_code: Business Logic Rule 002:\nMap city names to region codes.\n- Hanoi -> 'HN'\n- Ho Chi Minh City -> 'HCM'\n- Da Nang -> 'DN'\n- Anything else -> 'OT' (Other)",
    "source_type": "Code",
    "author": "Legacy Developer",
    "timestamp": "2026-04-24T14:39:22.736639Z",
    "metadata": {
      "business_rules": [],
      "raw_comments": [
        "# This function checks if the transaction ID follows the 2018 format: ",
        "# [YEAR]-[REGION]-[NUMERIC_ID]",
        "# Example: 2018-VN-0001",
        "# Note: 2019 data started using the new GUID format, but we still support the legacy one.",
        "# WARNING: This comment is misleading! ",
        "# This actually calculates VAT at 10%, but the code says it does 8%.",
        "# The AI Watchman should flag this discrepancy if possible.",
        "# Intentional discrepancy with comment"
      ]
    },
    "source_metadata": {},
    "schema_version": "v1"
  }
]